releases.name: Version 0.4.1
releases.body: Fixes an issue with Windows installer.

releases.name: Version 0.4.0
releases.body: Updated to the latest release of PokemonGo-Map, which includes support for the current PGO API.

releases.name: Version 0.3.4
releases.body: Updated to the new PokemonGo-Map, and added multiple account support and Google login.

releases.name: Version 0.3.3
releases.body: Updating PokemonGo-Map to latest build from main repo.

releases.name: Version 0.3.2
releases.body: Reverting to an older version of Electron, the newest release seems to have messed up some installations.

releases.name: Version 0.3.1
releases.body:
# THIS VERSION IS BROKEN

Fixes a bug with the map sometimes not initializing correctly. If you're experiencing an issue, re-install from this release.

releases.name: Version 0.3.0
releases.body:
# THIS VERSION IS BROKEN, DOWNLOAD 0.3.2

Major backend re-factoring, basing off [PokemonGoMap](https://github.com/PokemonGoMap/PokemonGo-Map) now.

Updates should be much easier now, since I don't have to modify the map code for each new release.

Google account support was removed for now, it will be added back in at a later time.

Official Linux support has been removed as of this release. With the Unknown6 bug, Python modules must be compiled and I don't have the resources to support more than OS X and Windows. If anyone wants to provide Linux support, I moved the build system to use Grunt so you should be able to add support via that.

releases.name: Version 0.2.1
releases.body: Fixing issues with Mac and Windows distributions not running correctly.

releases.name: Version 0.2.0
releases.body:
**NOTE: This release is broken, please use version 0.2.1.**

Fixes compatibility with new Pokemon GO API changes.

Linux users will need to install the Python 2 `xxhash` package using the following command:

```
sudo pip install xxhash
```

releases.name: Version 0.1.7
releases.body: Adding notice to main screen about outage.

releases.name: Version 0.1.6
releases.body:
Update map, including stat list and fix for API timeouts.

**Fast mode was removed due to Niantic API changes. Radius values should be 15 or lower due to slower scanning speeds.**

releases.name: Version 0.1.5
releases.body: Adding fast scan mode, fixing mobile sharing feature.

releases.name: Version 0.1.4
releases.body: New map update, changing asset delivery (should fix some of the map load errors), auto updates on Windows, donation buttons

releases.name: Version 0.1.3
releases.body: Updating to latest stable maps release (fixes notification bugs and should speed up scanning), reverting to ngrok for tunnel

releases.name: Version 0.1.2
releases.body:
Updates to map, including sound notifications and ability to change location without having to logout.

**Starting with this release, everyone will need their own Google Maps API key.**

[See the Wiki for info on generating your personal API key.](https://github.com/mchristopher/PokemonGo-DesktopMap/wiki/Google-Maps-API:-a-brief-guide-to-your-own-key)

releases.name: Version 0.1.1
releases.body: Fixes some loading bugs with Google Maps, switching to localtunnel.me for mobile since it doesn't have rate limits.

releases.name: Version 0.1.0
releases.body: Major update to map software, includes the latest release from the main repo. Also fixes logout issue with PTC (Google will still timeout after ~30 minutes).

releases.name: Version 0.0.7
releases.body: Adding the option to logout & change config options, and a server status indicator.

releases.name: Version 0.0.6
releases.body: Bug fixes, including issues with negative latitudes (southern hemisphere). Allows you to set the search radius.

releases.name: Version 0.0.5
releases.body: This release adds the ability to control what appears on the map, including PokeStops, and includes/excluding specific Pokemon.

releases.name: Version 0.0.4
releases.body: Fixes issues with python script in Windows, adds debug logging to developer console, fixes mobile support on Windows.

releases.name: Version 0.0.3
releases.body: This update adds mobile access support and fixes the problem with background processes not closing correctly.

releases.name: Second Release
releases.body: Adding Pokemon Trainer login support and the ability to set your location on the login screen.

releases.name: First Alpha Release
releases.body:
First alpha build of Pokemon Go Map desktop app.

Only works with Google authentication for now, Pokemon SSO coming soon.
